event today. Rather than speak about my business (BuBakes) I chose to speak 
about mental health. As I battle with severe anxiety, it wasn't the most 
polished speech - and at times I did lose my place, as the words I had 
written were jumping while my hands were shaking!"]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[]]></content:encoded></item><item><title>Karen Ramus, Executive Director of NAMI Austin, discusses 5/13/16</title><dc:creator>DCS</dc:creator><pubDate>Sat, 14 May 2016 05:01:18 +0000</pubDate><link>https://depressedcakeshop.org/Blog-articles/2016/5/13/d2gyww023sos5yjvyp6s9spp3olep6</link><guid isPermaLink="false">566232cae4b03851361248ab:5665fbc569492e52733023ac:5736b061ab48de6e3b4ac31f</guid><description><![CDATA[<img data-load="false" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/566232cae4b03851361248ab/1463202073661-3RVW5AHZWD55TPJRSL7Z/Screen+Shot+2016-05-13+at+10.00.59+PM.png?format=1000w" />]]></description><media:content type="image/png" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/566232cae4b03851361248ab/1570960832860-I0JZHQ49OKTZRGH48SOA/Screen+Shot+2019-10-13+at+11.00.03+AM.png?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="123" height="75"><media:title type="plain">Karen Ramus, Executive Director of NAMI Austin, discusses 5/13/16</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>Seattle Pacific University's NAMI chapter hosted an incredible pop-up last Friday!</title><dc:creator>DCS</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 03 May 2016 00:41:00 +0000</pubDate><link>https://depressedcakeshop.org/Blog-articles/2016/5/2/seattle-pacific-universitys-nami-chapter-hosted-an-incredible-pop-up-this-weekend</link><guid isPermaLink="false">566232cae4b03851361248ab:5665fbc569492e52733023ac:5727e27fe707ebe0b420c4f6</guid><description><![CDATA[<figure class="
