<p>Seattle Pacific University's NAMI chapter hosted a very successful pop-up on campus Friday, April 29th. They almost sold out of everything and made over $800 -- "which for selling things to poor college students, is really awesome" jokes one of the organizers, Carl Sallee.&nbsp;"It was crowded at the table almost the whole time and we spread a lot of awareness."&nbsp;</p>







  

  



  
    
      

        
          
            
              
